# SKILL_DESIGN_product-protection

**Type:** Skill
**Domain:** Design
**Version:** 1.0
**Status:** Active

---

## Purpose

Enforce product integrity rules during any image generation or compositing task.

Call this skill at the start of every compositing or generation task before defining environment, lighting, or props. It applies universally — regardless of which compositing protocol is selected.

---

## Core Rule

The product must remain **pixel-accurate and proportionally identical** to the source image.

---

## Do Not Alter

- Proportions
- Curvature or geometry
- Handles, lids, spouts, rivets, or structural components
- Branding or typography
- Metal grain or surface texture
- Highlights or shadows intrinsic to the product material
- Artificial gloss or CGI smoothing

---

## Allowed Adjustments Only

| Element | Allowed |
|---|---|
| Lighting | Yes — match to environment |
| Shadow | Yes — match to scene light direction |
| Color temperature | Yes — subtle, environment-driven |
| Environmental reflections | Yes — must align with light source direction |

Reflections and highlights must be consistent with the environmental light direction. No floating highlights or generic shine.

---

## Food Integration Addition

When food is present inside the vessel (Food-Integrated Protocol only):

- Food must conform naturally to container geometry
- Food must not float, intersect, or ignore physical boundaries of the vessel
- Food placement is the only additional adjustment allowed beyond the standard list above

---

## Trigger

Call at the start of:
- Master Lifestyle compositing
- High-End Editorial compositing
- Food-Integrated compositing
- Any generation task where a real product image is provided as source
